cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.IR 

The paper deals with detecting spam and malicious content on online social networks, specifically Twitter. This falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses techniques for analyzing the content of messages and predicting the trustworthiness of accounts, which are related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and data mining (cs.SD). The use of machine learning algorithms for detecting spam also falls under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the propagation of messages and interests of users, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and complex systems (cs.CY).
